                  <summary>Christian Sermons (<foreign xml:lang="ta">piracaṅkam</foreign>). A manuscript probably written and sent by the Jesuits of the Mission du Carnate at Pondicherry for the library of the king of France. Arrived in the library in 1738. The codex was bound in BnF library during the reign of Louis XVIII (1814-1824).</summary>
                  
